            <div class="large-12 columns">
            	<p><b>If this is an EMERGENCY situation, CALL 911 or contact the University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC) Police Department at (312) 355-5555. Do not use this form to report events that present an immediate threat to health or safety.</b><br />
<br />
If this matter is related to academic misconduct, <b>please use our <a href="http://go.uic.edu/AcademicIR" target=\"_blank\">Academic Integrity Incident Report Form</a>.</b><br />
<br />
The Office of the Dean of Students at the University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC) is charged with upholding the Student Disciplinary Policy, which identifies academic and behavioral expectations for all students on and off campus. If you have knowledge of an UIC student violating the Student Disciplinary Policy, you are encouraged to notify our office of the incident. It is important that you review our <a href="http://go.uic.edu/DisciplinaryPolicy" target=\"_blank\">Student Disciplinary Policy</a> to better understand our process and procedures for addressing student complaints.<br />
<br />
When completing this form, please be as thorough as possible to ensure your complaint is referred to the most appropriate place for review and follow up. <b>While anonymous complaints are accepted, the UniversityÂ’s ability to investigate and respond to anonymous complaints is limited.</b><br />
<br />
If you have any witnesses, individuals who are directly involved or observed the incident in question, whose perspective you would like contributed for consideration, please direct them to complete the <a href="http://go.uic.edu/WitnessForm" target=\"_blank\">Witness Statement Form</a>.<br />
<br />
If you have any questions regarding filing an incident report, please contact the Office of Dean of Students at (312) 996-4857 or dos@uic.edu.</p>            </div>
        </div>
